[h1]The While Loop[/h1]

The [b]while [/b]loop repeats through a block of code, as long as a specified condition is [b]true[/b].

[b]Syntax:[/b][code format="js"][b]while[/b] (condition) {    
   code block
}[/code]
[note]The [b]condition [/b]can be any conditional statement that returns true or false.[/note]

quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to print x's values from 1 to 5.
[!raw!]
var x = 1;
{0}(x <= {1}) {
    document.write(x + "<br />");
    x = {2} + 1;
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The While Loop[/h1]

Consider the following example.[code format="js" codeId="671"]var i=0;
[b]while [/b](i<=10) {
   document.write(i + "<br />");
   i++;
}[/code]
The loop will continue to run as long as i is less than, or equal to, 10. Each time the loop runs, it will increase by 1.

This will output the values from 0 to 10. [img id="2756" width="100%"]
